cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 250 miles WSW of Grand Cayman
cyclone.trajectory: moving ENE toward the Cayman Islands and central Cuba, then forecast to turn north-northeast across the Florida Keys/South Florida and curve north-northwest toward the eastern Gulf and west-central Florida coastline
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Keys or extreme South Florida

weather_observation.watch_coast: Sebastian Inlet FL southward around the Florida peninsula to Bonita Beach FL, including Lake Okeechobee, Florida Bay, the Keys
weather_observation.warning_coast: Cayman Islands, central Cuba provinces, Northwestern Bahamas
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Entire Florida peninsula including the Gulf Coast from the Keys northward to Tampa Bay and portions of the Atlantic coast
weather_observation.wind: Tropical-storm-force winds (35–45 mph) possible late Tuesday into Wednesday with higher gusts.
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor surge of 1–3 ft possible along the lower Tampa Bay–Port Manatee shoreline if onshore flow develops.
weather_observation.rainfall: Forecast totals of roughly 3–6 inches, locally higher, with periods of heavy downpours causing ponding and drainage issues.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Risk of isolated tornadoes, rough seas/large swells and rip currents that could interrupt vessel traffic and cargo operations.
